 Handler identity is independent of tool name and package version. Keep it stable across tool renames. Versions are exact positive integers, not semver ranges.
 
+## TUI presentation and re-entry
+
+Pi core owns the persistent deferred-work affordance. A compatible package can provide a full `presenter` and a short `summary`, but it must not mount or clear its own deferred widget. `summary` receives the neutral snapshot and a read-only context containing `cwd` and `sessionManager`; it must return privacy-safe text and must not expose tool arguments or package payloads. Core adds command guidance, renders the text, suppresses it while a full deferred UI owns input, restores it after Escape, and clears it as soon as `session.deferredBatch` is absent.
+
+Presentation selection is:
+
+| Capability | Full UI | Affordance after dismissal |
+|---|---|---|
+| Compatible presenter and summary | Package presenter | Package summary |
+| Compatible presenter without a summary | Package presenter | Core generic summary |
+| Missing or unavailable presenter | Core inspector | Core generic summary |
+| Presenter or summary throws | Core inspector for presenter failure; package presenter remains usable after summary failure | Core generic summary |
+
+`/deferred` opens the compatible package presenter and otherwise falls back to the core inspector. `/deferred inspect` always opens the core inspector, which provides Retry, Abandon, and Close. Package-specific commands and shortcuts can remain conveniences, but they are not the durable re-entry path. Core retries package presentation after reload, so restoring compatible package code recovers without changing journal state.
+
 ## Resolver operations
 
 `resolve` receives validated current parameters, the original tool-call ID, the current signal/context, and one operation:
@@ -161,7 +182,7 @@ The durability claim is limited to completed session append calls and process te
 
 | Mode | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| TUI | Uses a compatible package presenter, falling back to `/deferred`; held siblings render as not executed. |
+| TUI | Uses a compatible package presenter, keeps one core-owned re-entry affordance after dismissal, routes `/deferred` to package presentation, and reserves `/deferred inspect` for the generic inspector. |
 | SDK | Exposes snapshots/events and argument-free resume/abandon operations. |
 | RPC | Mirrors SDK with JSON `null`, capability discovery, typed errors, and settled operation responses. |
 | JSON | Emits initial `deferred_batch_state` after the session header and later `deferred_batch_changed` events. |
